nit: I encourage to create and write data to a temporary file and then rename the temporary file to COMPACT_POLICY_INFO_PATH file
Something like
File tempFile = new File(dataDir, COMPACT_POLICY_INFO_PATH + ".temp");
if (!tempFile.exists()) {
    tempFile.createNewFile();
}
objectMapper.defaultPrettyPrintingWriter().writeValue(tempFile, compactionPolicySwitchInfo);
tempFile.renameTo(new File(dataDir, COMPACT_POLICY_INFO_PATH);

The reason to use a temporary file and rename it after is that POSIX guarantees file rename is an atomic operation, but not the file write. The json file is pretty small so that file writing should be atomic, but it's just a good pattern to follow.

